==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in 1644. Perhaps a {{back-form|abomination|nocap=1|lang=en}}.<ref>{{R:CDOE|page=4}}</ref> Alternatively, perhaps from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|abōminātus}}, past participle of {{m|la|abōminarī||to deprecate as an ill omen}}, from {{term|ab|lang=la}} + {{term|ominari||to forebode, presage|lang=la}}, from {{term|omin-||omen|lang=la}}.<ref>{{R:MW3 1976|page=5}}</ref>

