===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{context|rare|lang=en}} [[abominable|Abominable]]; [[detest]]ed. {{defdate|First attested in the late 16<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=6}}</ref>

===Verb===
{{en-verb|abominat}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To feel [[disgust]] towards; to [[abhor]]; to [[loathe]] or [[detest]] thoroughly; to [[hate]] in the highest degree, as if with religious [[dread]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* ''"Much as I '''abominate''' writing, I would not give up Mr. Collins's correspondence for any consideration."'' ([http://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Pride_and_Prejudice Pride and Prejudice])
# {{context|transitive|colloquial|lang=en}} To dislike strongly. {{defdate|First attested in the late 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>

